@ThinkingandTinkering There are stepper motors that use an iron rotor instead of magnets, so called "variable reluctance" stepper motors 
I just saw your toothed rotor and it reminded me of the simplified diagrams for these vr steppers, of course yours has the flux concentrated in one "tooth" rather than the flux flowing from one tooth to another on the opposing side

There was another comment here about a bicycle wheel in this configuration, I think that's a very neat idea - just wondering if using magnets in the rotor would help or hinder performance?
